 10  # Intervals
 11  
 12  In any preorder `α`, we define intervals (which on each side can be either infinite, open, or
 13  closed) using the following naming conventions:
 14  - `i`: infinite
 15  - `o`: open
 16  - `c`: closed
 17  
 18  Each interval has the name `I` + letter for left side + letter for right side. For instance,
 19  `Ioc a b` denotes the inverval `(a, b]`.
 20  
 21  This file contains these definitions, and basic facts on inclusion, intersection, difference of
 22  intervals (where the precise statements may depend on the properties of the order, in particular
 23  for some statements it should be `linear_order` or `densely_ordered`).
 24  
 25  This file also contains statements on lower and upper bounds of intervals.
 26
